        <Parent_String>bodies of freshwater by biome [300387629], bodies of freshwater [300387627], bodies of water (natural) [300266059], natural landscapes [300132294], landscapes (environments) [300008626], Settlements and Landscapes (hierarchy name) [300008346], Built Environment (hierarchy name) [300264550], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Large category including areas of land characterized by poor drainage, standing or slowly moving water, and as a result, an almost constant state of water-saturated soil. Wetlands include swamps, marshes, and bogs.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Weit gefasste Kategorie, die Landflächen beinhaltet, die durch schlechte Entwässerung, stehendes oder sich nur sehr langsam bewegendes Wasser und als Resultat daraus durch ein nahezu immer wassergesättigtes Erdreich gekennzeichnet sind. Hierzu zählen Moore, Marschland und Sümpfe.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
